VERSION 1
WHEN PRESENT \b(?:system|popen|exec|execp|CreateProcess)\b\s*\(
WHEN EXPR MISSING:validate|sanitize|allowlist|whitelist|escapeShellArg
REPORT AS area_of_interest
REASON Detects the usage of command execution functions that may introduce command injection risks and unauthorized access to system resources.
TRACE Externalized rule logic for Unsafe Use of Command Execution Functions.
